author: Sports Staff
title: Non-league Lincoln City snatch late winner at Burnley to write themselves into FA Cup history | The Independent
text:
Non-league Lincoln City stunned Burnley at Turf Moor on Saturday afternoon, winning 1-0 to become the first non-league team to reach the quarter-finals of the FA Cup in 103 years.
Sean Raggett nodded home for the National League side in the 88th minute to send the minnows into the last eight of the competition.
Burnley had dominated possession but ultimately failed to break Danny Cowley's spirited side down, before Raggett scored with Lincoln's solitary shot on goal.
More to follow.
